Gunmen on Sunday night attacked two separate communities in Kaduna State and killed four persons. The assailants also wounded eight persons and abducted two others. The first attack was in Kutura Station in Tantatu Ward of Kajuru Local Government Area where four persons were killed and eight others wounded. The second attack was in Gwagwada  of Chikun Local Government Area Sunday night where two persons were said to have been abducted. A source yesterday said the eight persons wounded at Kutura were receiving treatment in an undisclosed hospital. The gunmen were said to have attacked Kutura community at about 8:00pm and opened  fire on a group of youths  who were celebrating ahead of the new year. Details of the attack at Gwagwada were, however, sketchy. When contacted, the spokesman of the state police command, Yakubu Sabo, confirmed the incident at Kutura, saying four persons were killed and three injured. He said: “Yesterday (Sunday),  at about 2.45am, some unknown gunmen, in Kutura hamlet in Kayana village in Kajuru Local Government Area of Kaduna State while some villagers were conducting a new year party. opened fire on the villagers. “They killed four people and injured three.  Police, on receipt of the information went to the Area and evacuated the victims and engaged in vigorous search for the suspects.” He said men of the Special Anti-Robbery Squard (SARS) and conventional men from the Kaduna Division had been mobilised to the area to ensure that the perpetrators were brought to book. While expressing the condolence of the Commissioner of Police, Ahmad Abdurahman, to the families of the victims,  he assured that the police would do everything possible within the ambit of the law to protect lives and property of the citizenry.